1 AN ACT relating to certified public accountant firms.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 ïƒ¢Section 1. KRS 325.380 is amended to read as follows:
4 (1) No person shall assume or use the title or designation "certified public accountant,"
5 "public accountant," or the abbreviation "CPA" or any other title, designation,
6 words, letters, abbreviation, sign, card, or device tending to indicate that the person
7 is a certified public accountant, unless the person holds a license issued under this
8 chapter or qualifies for a practice privilege under KRS 325.282.
9 (2) No firm shall assume or use the title or designation "certified public accountants,"
10 "public accountants," or the abbreviation "CPA's" or any other title, designation,
11 words, letters, abbreviation, sign, card, or device tending to indicate that the firm is
12 composed of certified public accountants, unless the firm:
13 (a) Holds a license issued under this chapter which has not been revoked or
14 suspended, and all offices of the firm in this state are maintained as required
15 under this chapter; or
16 (b) Is authorized to do so as provided for in KRS 325.301.
17 (3) No individuals or firm shall assume or use the title or designation "certified
18 accountant," "chartered accountant," "enrolled accountant," "licensed accountant,"
19 "registered accountant," "accredited auditor," "accounting practitioner," "accredited
20 accountant," "expert accountant," "expert auditor," "certified auditor," or any other
21 title or designation likely to be confused with "certified public accountant" and
22 "public accountant" or any of the abbreviations "CA," "AP," "PA," "RA," "LA," or
23 "AA" or similar abbreviations likely to be confused with "CPA."
24 (4) No person or firm shall sign or affix his or her name or a firm name to any
25 document or prepare or issue any document which indicates that the person or firm
26 performed attest services or that includes any language which indicates that the
27 person or the firm has expert knowledge in performing attest services, unless the
